  <header>
    <h1>MemoryMinder</h1>
    <p>An inclusive mobile app for early-stage Alzheimer’s — memory aid, routines, and caregiver support.</p>
  </header>

  <div class="wrap">
    <!-- Cover / collage placeholder -->
    <div class="heroimg">Place product cover / screens collage here</div>
    <p class="caption">Tip: export a hero image from Figma (PNG/JPG) and replace this placeholder.</p>

    <!-- Overview -->
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Problem</h3>
        <p>Early-stage Alzheimer’s gradually impairs memory and day-to-day functioning. Existing apps rarely focus on dementia workflows and often prioritize education over practical support for daily tasks.</p>
        <div class="kv">
          <div><strong>Domain:</strong> Dementia care</div>
          <div><strong>Type:</strong> Mobile app (iOS/Android)</div>
          <div><strong>Focus:</strong> Everyday assistance & safety</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Outcome</h3>
        <p><em>MemoryMinder</em> simplifies routines and supports independence through reminders, medication tracking, and symptom logging with trends and resources. Usability testing achieved an average <strong>SUS 87.5 (Grade A)</strong> across participants.</p>
        <div class="tags">
          <span class="tag">Reminders</span>
          <span class="tag">Medication</span>
          <span class="tag">Symptom Tracking</span>
          <span class="tag">Accessible UI</span>
          <span class="tag">Care Support</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Role & Team -->
    <h2>Role & Team</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p><strong>Team:</strong> Xiao Yu, Shruthika Sridharan, Prachi Modi</p>
      <p><strong>Course:</strong> INF 385T Inclusive Design • <strong>Timeline:</strong> 8–10 weeks (Fall 2023)</p>
      <p><strong>My contributions:</strong> user flows & IA, low/mid‑fi prototyping, concept testing, SUS evaluation, and synthesis.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Process -->
    <h2>Process</h2>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Empathy</h3>
        <p>Literature review, mind mapping, and competitive scan to understand Alzheimer’s challenges and existing solutions.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Define</h3>
        <p>Affinity mapping → user needs → HMWs → persona for early‑stage Alzheimer’s. MVP prioritized everyday tasks, accessible content, and tracking.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Ideate</h3>
        <p>User flows, information architecture, sketches, low‑fi prototypes, and concept testing with caregivers.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Prototype</h3>
        <p>Mid‑fi prototypes with clear hierarchy, readable typography (≥14pt), and consistent components.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Test</h3>
        <p>Task‑based usability tests (add to‑do, add symptom, add medication) and SUS survey with four participants of mixed tech proficiency.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Key flows -->
    <h2>Key Flows</h2>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>1) Add a Plan / Medication</h3>
        <p>From Home, add a plan or medication with time, frequency, and reminder options. Calendar shows tasks by day; completion triggers contextual confirmation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>2) Track a Symptom</h3>
        <p>Select a symptom category, log details (time, intensity, response), then review color‑coded trends and related resources.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- IA -->
    <h2>Information Architecture</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p><strong>Top‑level:</strong> Scheduler (Tasks & Medication), Track (Symptoms), Feed (Resources), Account (Settings / Caregiver).</p>
      <div class="heroimg">Place IA diagram image here</div>
      <p class="caption">Replace with an exported IA diagram.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Screens (placeholders) -->
    <h2>Representative Screens</h2>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card"><strong>Dashboard</strong><div class="heroimg">Dashboard screen</div></div>
      <div class="card"><strong>Calendar / To‑do</strong><div class="heroimg">Calendar view</div></div>
      <div class="card"><strong>Add Medication</strong><div class="heroimg">Form screen</div></div>
      <div class="card"><strong>Symptoms Graph</strong><div class="heroimg">Charts</div></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Usability -->
    <h2>Usability Results</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <ul>
        <li><strong>SUS average:</strong> 87.5 / 100 (Grade A – Highly Usable).</li>
        <li>Users completed core tasks easily but wanted clearer medication onboarding and more legible graphs.</li>
        <li>Redundant Home vs. To‑do surfaced; we kept Dashboard as the entry point and used Calendar for drill‑down.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Learnings / Next -->
    <h2>What I Learned</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Prioritize MVP:</strong> focus scope to ship and learn faster.</li>
        <li><strong>Accessibility by default:</strong> readable type, contrast, guidance, and reduced cognitive load are critical.</li>
        <li><strong>Evidence‑informed design:</strong> when direct access to users is limited, systematic literature and competitive reviews help.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>Next Steps</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <ul>
        <li>Caregiver access (shared data entry & reminders).</li>
        <li>Community features for safe peer support.</li>
        <li>Location tracking for outdoor safety.</li>
        <li>Hi‑fi design and validation with target users.</li>
      </ul>
